			>
			<DIV></DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>"What does that have to do with how many hp's I can buff myself? You're confusing the issue, what the heck right to warriors have to cleric- type abilities?"</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Gee, and I thought SK's got a self-buff that looks suspiciously like a priest spell. They do, don't they.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Come on guy, you can do better than that -</DIV>
<DIV>What the hesk right does any TANK have to 90% ressing, Clerical buffs, or FD pulling. Those are all pretty out of class character for a Tank. Or are some classes TanksPLUS?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Classes are getting re-envisionsed Josahd.&nbsp;That doesn't just mean Knights getting upgrades so they can tank all single-group content interchanably with the Primary Tank. But that's also going to mean upgrades to Warriors so we aren't totally blown away in an environment where Knights got upgrades to achieve interchangable tanking AND keep a vast amount of utility as a free bonus.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Not is it only fairer for Warriors to share more in the common pool of abilities (that's the place Knight's looked to discover their entitlement to an avoidance/mitigation discipine) SoE finds apropriate for Tanks to have it's also consistant with reducing impediments and making the game more fun for all of us to play.</DIV><p>Message Edited by Battleblade-Xegony on <span class=date_text>06-27-2005</span> <span class=time_text>07:11 AM</span>	
		</td></tr>
