		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Battleblade-Xegony wrote:<BR>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>"What does that have to do with how many hp's I can buff myself? You're confusing the issue, what the heck right to warriors have to cleric- type abilities?"</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Gee, and I thought SK's got a self-buff that looks suspiciously like a priest spell. They do, don't they.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Come on guy, you can do better than that -</DIV>
<DIV>What the hesk right does any TANK have to 90% ressing, Clerical buffs, or FD pulling. Those are all pretty out of class character for a Tank. Or are some classes TanksPLUS?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>The SK self-Buff was given specifically because all hybrid classes received a special buff line that was unique to their class and not shared by the parent class. This buff is reflective of the Paladin's Brells, the Ranger buff and the BL buff. Warriors were given HP AAs specifically to counteract the effect of hybrid Tank Self-Buffs. If those are not effective enough then they should be further increased.</P>
<P>One could also ask what right does any TANK have to Dual Wieldable weapons, higher melee DPS, higher offensive skills, etc etc. How can you say that a classic Paladin having Clerical spells is out of class character? or that a Shadow Knight having Nercomatic spells is pretty out of class character?</P>
<P>Really if you want to banter about things like Paladin Buffs and 90% rezes I can come up with some more acceptable solutions like:</P>
<P>When a player dies they generate a no-drop life crystal on their corpse, this gets destroyed if they are rezzed, but if not it can be looted by a player and then used to receive an XP rez at a later date.</P>
<P>A line of Buffs for Druids and Shamans that conflict with Clerical buffs could easily be used to lessen the effects of Paladin buffs in groups by allowing them more options, and still hold value to Paladin buffs.</P>	
		</td></tr>
