<img src="/eq/i/icons/Classes/warrior.gif" border=0 alt=""/></a><br>
			


			
			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=warriorbalance&message.id=6557#M6557">180</a> of 721
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 564 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>BruennorB wrote:<BR></P>
<P><EM>Hmm, so pulling the pets solo is an exploit, was wondering about that. But even if a person pulled all 3, a warrior is the only person who can tank all 3 at one time as each one hits for 2k and one flurries, that is all I am gonna say on that.</EM></P>
<P>Yeah, it's an exploit, the event is designed to force all 3 mobs to frenzy on the person who is aggro on the most damaged mob.&nbsp;&nbsp; By using zone geometry (the gate to her room being smaller than the mobs, and the distance between the mobs) to separate the mobs from one another, they are prevented from doing what they were designed to do.&nbsp;&nbsp; </P>
<P>Once the event is done the way it's supposed to, it's not a 6 man encounter, it's a raid.&nbsp;&nbsp; I have no problem with accepting that warriors ARE the dominant raid boss tank, thus this is clearly within the pramaters of a warrior's responsibility.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Furthermore, just because something is difficult for a Knight doesn't make it impossible.&nbsp;&nbsp; Knights can tank the 3 babies.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Certainly at a higher risk, but they can do it.&nbsp;&nbsp; The gap in soloability is *absolutely* insurmountable.&nbsp;&nbsp; The warrior cannot create conditions which enable him to solo "big game" as the Knight can with tanking "raid targets".&nbsp;&nbsp; There's a large gap between "Kind of a pain to do" and "Impossible".</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P><BR><EM>Frodlin, I am curious, what gear lv are you talking about when you say if warriors got a solo upgrade that made them as far apart as knights and warriors are on raid? Just about Everything in tacvi can 1 round me. Some things in anguish can 1 round me if I get unlucky. </EM></P>
<P>The dirty little secret Bruennor, is every one of those mobs that can one round you... can also one round me.&nbsp;&nbsp; In Tacvi, and a couple mobs in Anguish can just as easily one round me as they can you, once defensive is up.&nbsp;&nbsp; The only mobs where I have an actual insurmountable advantage in EQ tanking are the Anguish Augment droppers, and Keldovan the Harrier, because I simply do not have to tank them without defensive, or defensive lasts until he's slowed.&nbsp;&nbsp; The rest, I most certainly DO have to tank without defensive, and I can be just as 1 rounded as you can.&nbsp; I've been 1 rounded by most mobs in Tacvi, and have been 1 rounded by Keldovan (as well as the Specialization mob, and one of the Adaptation forms), as well as against all mastruqs in Tacvi.&nbsp;&nbsp; </P>
<P>The fact that someone can get one rounded doesnt' preclude them from tanking, otherwise no one would do or have done Tacvi or gotten to Anguish.&nbsp;&nbsp; You take your chances, and usually come out on top by minimizing those chances.&nbsp; </P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P><EM>Also, the saying that if you can live through 1 round you can tank the mob doesnt really hold true in eq. That is all dependant on whether or not you have enough clerics to keep up a 1 sec cheal chain for the most part, so you will have clerics chaining it non stop assuming you have 10 clerics, which my guild hasnt had, save once in a blue moon, in years. It is also dependant on the cleric getting a crit cheal, otherwise a mob that can almost 1 round you will be able to 1 round you the round cheal doesnt hit for full. </EM></P>
<P>That of course is assuming that you're doing a CH rotation... which not all guilds do, mine pretty much never does them.&nbsp; Last time we did Tacvi, we did it with 3 clerics online.&nbsp;&nbsp; It also assumes there's zero spamming.&nbsp;&nbsp; But on top of all of that, the point is it's indeed possible, even jumping through hoops.&nbsp;&nbsp; No amount of jumping through hoops makes it possible for a warrior to solo a lot of NPC's that Knights can solo.&nbsp;&nbsp; Again, the gulf is between "doable with effort" and "not doable at all", and that's not an acceptable gap.&nbsp; I want the ability to jump through hoops and be able to succeed on solo targets, just like you have the ability to jump through hoops and be able to succeed vs. raid targets.&nbsp;&nbsp; </P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P><EM>I am not top of the line geared, I buff to 14.2k/2850, and still have some weak slots, but a majority of my gear isnt shabby. My guild wiped on keldovan 2 days ago for the first time in ages, surprised us =P. Anyway, when keldovan got to me, I didnt last 3 seconds. Didnt have time to target myself and loh to try to buy some folks more time to log. The 1 rounding arguement worked in time as very few mobs had really high attack, but nowadays, too many mobs hit rather high spikes, and hit for 4k+, on knights and dont allow them leeway that your skills do. Also you hint at how many mobs are knight tankable now. How many of the ones you are hinting at are old content? Are you going to hold it against high end knights that they can tank yelinak and creator? Could use some enlightening on your exact thoughts on this particular dicussion piece.</EM><BR><BR></P>
<P>I'd say that Keldovan, and the Anguish aug droppers are pretty much the only "warrior only" mobs in EQ, because the advantage that a warrior has is his ability to annihilate the mob's offense through the majority of "danger time".&nbsp;&nbsp; </P>
<P>After that, maybe Tunat, if you're smart enough to do a defensive rotation on him.&nbsp; The rest of EQ is completely knight tankable given enough work.&nbsp;&nbsp; On the other hand, the gap in soloability is absolutely and completely insurmountable.&nbsp; I'm fine with 7 mobs being only able to be soloed by Knights and the rest being able to be soloed by both given enough effort.</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P><BR><EM>Now I got a question for you Frodlin. What is this raid design that gives knights specific jobs? What jobs are there that are made only for knights, that nobody else can do?</EM> </P>
<P>Whoah whoah whoah... there's a HUGE difference between "only doable by knights" and "Best done by Knights".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pretty much all offtanking is best done by knights.&nbsp; Particularly in stuff that requires a combination of Non Damage tanking and other forms of CC like Root etc.&nbsp; Having roles which are designed for you isn't the same as having roles which are exclusive to you.&nbsp; You most certainly DO have roles which are designed for you.&nbsp;&nbsp; You cannot tell me that you use warriors to tank Hanvar adds, or Keldo adds, or you use warriors for Pre-CC purposes on Kretv/Tavas, or that you use warriors to offtank Ukun Juxtapincers (unless you're really really into lowering efficiency), or warriors to tank Foresight Dragorns (again, unless you're REALLY into taking damage on stun lockable mobs), or that you use warriors for anything but standin in line waiting to tank bosses.&nbsp;&nbsp; you're not seriously trying to tell me that a Paladin with a grieg's end hammer isn't the premier Ramp tank in EQ, or that on heavy AE mobs or cure necessary mobs that you're using someone else for those roles.</P>
<P>If a raid underuses knights, then they're ridiculous, but that doesn't mean the content isn't designed to best use their skills.&nbsp; The content most certainly IS used to best utilize Knights' skills.</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P><BR><BR><EM>You mention parity doesnt mean sameness, I am glad you understand that. Do me a favor and explain that to all your buddies on these boards when knights are talking about group parity. Just so you know, yes, my guild uses warriors to tm, and they do a fine job of it to. In my book when it comes to solo'ing, grouping, and raiding it currently looks like this<BR><BR>Warrior<BR>&lt; = &gt;<BR><BR>Knights<BR>&gt; = &lt;</EM><BR><BR>That's not at all what it "looks like" in reality.&nbsp; There's 2 diferent areas of grouping, and the power gap in favor of knights is HUGE in the majority of grouping scenarios.&nbsp; It would go like this:</P>
<P>1. Solo for exp, 2. Big Game Soloing 3. Grouping vs. MPG and below level mobs 4. grouping in RSS+ level mobs 5. Raid offtanking roles 6. Raid boss mob tanking</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>Knight </P>
<P>1. &gt;&gt;&nbsp; 2 &gt;&gt;&gt; 3. &gt; 4. = 5. &gt; 6. &lt;&lt;</P>
<P>Warrior</P>
<P>1. &lt;&lt; 2. &lt;&lt;&lt; 3. &lt; 4. = 5. &lt; 6. &gt;&gt;</P>
<P>That's not balanced at all</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P><BR>Tell me, why do warriors deserve = = &gt; while knights would be = = &lt; ?</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>Warriors deserve the same number of &gt; as we have &lt;&nbsp; We're WAY behind at the moment, and that's ONLY in terms of tanking and has nothing to do with the bazillion othr roles.</P></BLOCKQUOTE><BR>
<DIV></DIV>
