<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
KAhm wrote:<BR><BR>
<P>The SK self-Buff was given specifically because all hybrid classes received a special buff line that was unique to their class and not shared by the parent class. This buff is reflective of the Paladin's Brells, the Ranger buff and the BL buff. Warriors were given HP AAs specifically to counteract the effect of hybrid Tank Self-Buffs. If those are not effective enough then they should be further increased.</P>
<P>
<HR>
</P>
<P>from&nbsp; eq rankings :</P>
<P>top&nbsp; warrior&nbsp; :gster mactruckk :luclin server :16088 hp 1692attack 3108&nbsp; ac </P>
<P>top&nbsp;&nbsp;ranger :nendiilya erinyes:luclin server:12730 hp 1701attack 2390&nbsp; ac</P>
<P>top&nbsp;&nbsp;paladin : chingerz angsantos:saryn&nbsp; server:13901 hp 1586&nbsp;attack 2806 ac </P>
<P>top&nbsp; shadowknight : skaxx verita`scura:fennin ro&nbsp; server:14032hp 1588 attack 2739&nbsp; ac </P>
<P>ranked&nbsp; by&nbsp; hitpoints . </P>
<P>the&nbsp; difference in&nbsp;UNBUFFED&nbsp;hitpoints&nbsp;isn't&nbsp;significant&nbsp;enough to counter the hybrids&nbsp;ability&nbsp;to&nbsp;lf and otherbuff and&nbsp;self or&nbsp;otherheal&nbsp;during&nbsp;combat. </P>
<P>perhaps&nbsp;something as&nbsp; simple as making the hp aa ability&nbsp; open ended&nbsp; and 5&nbsp; aa's(the cost of each level of aa) for each&nbsp; rune a&nbsp;non&nbsp; pure melee &nbsp;turns in up&nbsp; to&nbsp; the&nbsp;maximum quantity&nbsp; of runes&nbsp; per&nbsp; level of&nbsp; the non&nbsp; pure melee classes .&nbsp; </P>
<P>&nbsp; </P></BLOCKQUOTE><BR>
