			<BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
togam wrote:<BR><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
KAhm wrote:<BR><BR>
<P>The SK self-Buff was given specifically because all hybrid classes received a special buff line that was unique to their class and not shared by the parent class. This buff is reflective of the Paladin's Brells, the Ranger buff and the BL buff. Warriors were given HP AAs specifically to counteract the effect of hybrid Tank Self-Buffs. If those are not effective enough then they should be further increased.</P>
<P>
<HR>

<P></P>
<P>from&nbsp; eq rankings :</P>
<P>top&nbsp; warrior&nbsp; :gster mactruckk :luclin server :16088 hp 1692attack 3108&nbsp; ac </P>
<P>top&nbsp;&nbsp;ranger :nendiilya erinyes:luclin server:12730 hp 1701attack 2390&nbsp; ac</P>
<P>top&nbsp;&nbsp;paladin : chingerz angsantos:saryn&nbsp; server:13901 hp 1586&nbsp;attack 2806 ac </P>
<P>top&nbsp; shadowknight : skaxx verita`scura:fennin ro&nbsp; server:14032hp 1588 attack 2739&nbsp; ac </P>
<P>ranked&nbsp; by&nbsp; hitpoints . </P>
<P><FONT color=#ffff00>the&nbsp; difference in&nbsp;UNBUFFED&nbsp;hitpoints&nbsp;isn't&nbsp;significant&nbsp;enough to counter the hybrids&nbsp;ability&nbsp;to&nbsp;lf and otherbuff and&nbsp;self or&nbsp;otherheal&nbsp;during&nbsp;combat. </FONT></P>
<P>perhaps&nbsp;something as&nbsp; simple as making the hp aa ability&nbsp; open ended&nbsp; and 5&nbsp; aa's(the cost of each level of aa) for each&nbsp; rune a&nbsp;non&nbsp; pure melee &nbsp;turns in up&nbsp; to&nbsp; the&nbsp;maximum quantity&nbsp; of runes&nbsp; per&nbsp; level of&nbsp; the non&nbsp; pure melee classes .&nbsp; </P>
<P> </P></BLOCKQUOTE><BR>
<DIV></DIV><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE><BR>
<DIV>That is where I'm looking. This isn't fair, and should be made up in the warrior's abilities, and or HP/AC bonuses. This is why I say a Warrior's Strengths are getting weaker as the upgrades and expansions come out. I think this Togam hit the most important point of all this Knight vs. Warrior stuff. The difference in HP and AC is not significant enough for a warrior to be desirable vs. environment group wise. A boost in these area's and maybe including some offensive (Heavy hitter description). </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The idea is to get the HP/AC/DPS up to where the Warrior is at least equal in group content. Adding a little to each would not make a super class, and if well thought out could actually *Fix* alot of problems. Snare weapons, Some shields with an added bonus to Stun/slam an oppenant, these could help a warrior in the utility area without really giving a warrior utility. Maybe fighting with a weapon with the intent of snaring (Aiming for the legs) could be implemented, and DPS would of course drop while *Trying* for a successfull blow to the knee, etc.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I truely beleive giving us some gimp type utilities isn't gonna fix a problem, when the utilities are shared by alot of classes, that ussually one in the group&nbsp;has&nbsp;anyways. I think giving us these same Utilities will actually hurt some other classes that are already having a hard enough time finding a group (Rangers, Druids, Chanters, If not for KEI, Shammy's would rule, since not many places CC is really needed anymore, even rogues, since most groupable content don't need a rogue to unlock, find traps, etc). When thinking of these utilities, keep in mind their are some other class's with sincere problems that are very similar to the warrior's, and giving us the only thing they have to get a group, is gonna really hit them hard. If the Warrior can snare, why bother getting a druid or a ranger, or even a Wizzy? Get a Monk, Mage and Beastie. Better DPS. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>A group don't need a snarer now, if the MT is an SK. Don't need CC now, if the MT is a Pally. The Warrior MT is their hope of getting a group. Or the Opposing Knight class. They have a two in one chance of being needed in a group as it stands, giving a warrior these abilities would make it a 1 in 3 chance. This is why I have a problem with alot of the stuff proposed. I think giving Druids and other classes heals compatible with Clerics is gonna hit a cleric hard as well too. We need to be thinking of these things as well. When you balance out a class, your not looking at just three classes, there are several class's in the game that are directly effected, not just the Knights, when you start adding utilities to Warriors.</DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
