<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>D: HP/AC in group content is not needed, no. But if it was substantially easier to keep a warrior alive, it would make a difference. Goes hand in hand with the above. IF all three were increased enough to show a difference, it would mean something to the cleric that may be lagging (Like myself in the warrior department), which are out there. I have a level 54 cleric, and can keep you alive in all content, but I can keep any tank alive in all content, providing I don't run out of mana. If the mana I use in comparison between the three is greatly reduced by having a Warrior in heavier content, I would depending on my mana pool be influenced between the easier mana drain and the added benefits from having an other than Warrior in group. If I get a Warrior, my mana isn't in jeapardy. If I recieve a Pally, then maybe he can help me. If I chose an SK, he will need to be aware of my inabilities (being level 54 in higher group content maybe), and lifetap a bit more. These are all decisions that I dont' make at this time. I could keep a knight alive in POV just as easily as I can a Warrior. Neither needing to worry about lifetap, or extra heals, and this was at level 46 (I did the trial&nbsp;of execution&nbsp;in POJ soon as I turned 46). </DIV>
