			"Gee, and I thought SK's got a self-buff that looks suspiciously like a priest spell. They do, don't they."<br><br>Find me a priest spell that looks remotely like Cloak of Discord.  Go for it.  Actually, look at the history of it.  Due to a bug, pally shielding line (aura of whatever), ended up stacking with the conviction line.  For some reason they left it in the game.  Eventually, warriors were given 500 hp from aa's to compensate for this.  Later, around the time omens came out, the devs realized the one class getting screwed by all of this was shadowknights, so they changed our cloak line from a buff that blocked every other hybrid hp spells (since all hybrids have a varient of it), to one that stacked with all other hybrid hp spells.  You've already gotten your compensation for this ability.  You have an extra 500 hp unbuffed, that doesn't take up a buff slot, and isn't dispellable, to make up for my 350 hp and 49 AC.  Actually, depending on what buffs you have, the AC and DS gap is more like... zero, and you maintain a 150 hp advantage.  I'm sure you've heard of Guard of Earth?  If not, talk to a friendly ranger, or look it up on Lucy.  If there's not a ranger around... well, you still get to keep that 150 hp advantage.  And you don't have to get level 70 runes to get access to it.  And, oh, by the way, my hp buff isn't anywhere near the near clone of conviction you're asking for.<br><br>Oh yeah, one of my parent classes CAN buff hitpoints.  Can one of yours?  Didn't think so.<br><br>That was a really, really week attempt to discredit just one of my points.  C'mon, can't you do better than that?
