		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>No Zell, you miss the whole point of the "parity" movement.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The Prime Healer is almost guaranteed a group. Let's pretend Druids and Shaman are <U>just healers</U> too or that Clerics are in short supply. Wouldn't it be FUN for us Druids and Shaman to be capable group healers (and make MANY Clerics who really can only heal no longer even log in excet to raid or be botted)?? Sure, we can nuke, DoT, sane, Root, slow, spot heal, debuff, etc. BBBBbbbbbut err um We Only Get Groups as Main Healers and Need to Do All Single Group Content Interchangably with the Prime Healer or or or we'll hold our breath!!</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The Primary Tank is almost guaranteed a group. Let's pretned Knights don't have powerful ancillary skills that give us prefernce in ALL but the most difficult content. If PART warriors aren't allowed to do the most difficult content interchangably with the Primary Tank we'll hold our breath!!</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>"Course the more I read the more I find many warriors don't seem like your ideas BB"</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Absolparkingtively!!! I DARE SoE to do a survey of Warriors and find out how many think Warriors should have Tanking Superiority and how many think we should have compensatory utility because it was taken away. I KNOW that I and Frodlin may be the only two Warriors in the game that feel we as a class have no choice - utility it is. We may disagree what the utility should be, but I'm certain sure we both agree SoE will not remove the snare from Stonewall and cut it's refresh in half.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Tank Superiority ended for the former Primary Tank two expansions ago and I've lgged in to group with my 2700AC 14K HP unbuffed 70 Warrior to group ONCE in the last month. Sir I have 500 days played on just the Warrior. It takes some major $%^$ to induce me not to log on. (I have played my 55 Paladin twink some, but it's just depressing to note how powerful he's become.)</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>"Course how is getting knight abilities lead to tanking parity?"</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I'm sure you realize I'm talking utility parity. Yep, I need to dependably stop runners and gaters, heal myself during combat, recover HP's in a reasonable amount of time between kills, have a resonable chance to pul singles, etc. These are abilities that ALL classes that tank should have.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Yes, I've proposed a couple of Warrior Unique Disciplines (mostly cribed from the Openings System we never got that should have been a collection of short duration/short refresh disciplines in the first place) like:</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>
<DIV>Rally</DIV>
<DIV>You find the inner resources to re-double your efforts</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Endurance cost: 250</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Duration: 2 ticks</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Refresh: 30 ticks</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Increase Increase Haste (no cap) by 10%</DIV>
<DIV><BR>Rallying Cry</DIV>
<DIV>You inspire your group to greater aggressiveness</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Endurance cost: 300/tick</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Duration:&nbsp;1 ticks</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Refresh: 30 ticks</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Increase damage modifier by 10% Group V1</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Cover</DIV>
<DIV>You gain the ability to help shield your companions</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Endurance cost: 300/tick</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Refresh 30 ticks</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Duration 2 ticks</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Absorb 50% of all melee damage directed at all group members</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Decrease Melee mitigation by 20%</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV></DIV>
<DIV>But basically anything central that distinguished Warriors from Knights, say unmatched survivability (not being needed to be healed a little less, but lives when others die) and being the only class that tanks with an avoidance/mitigation disciple, they put on their shopping list and SoE gave it to them.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Parity is not just parity in Warrior Tanking.</DIV><p>Message Edited by Battleblade-Xegony on <span class=date_text>06-27-2005</span> <span class=time_text>06:38 PM</span>	
