		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>"I don't see why we should dilute the roles of buffing classes."</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>In reviewing the Cleric board, they got an indication that the Developers were concerned about the buffers in PoK. One suggestion was that buffs fade faster if you are not grouped with a class capable of casting a buff you are using - most didn't think that was a great idea and an alternative was proposed that really wasn't much different.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The problems for Warriors in a nutshell is that we are in competition with a Buffing Class and I might add a Buffing, Ressing, and Healing Class. Now that's all well and good if Warriors had ancillary skills up to that VERY high quality. But frankly, I can't think of any at all. Death Touch?? Zone Kill???</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I'm absolutely certain how Paladins would react if SoE gave Clerics a Taunt button and some tanking improvements and had Paladins and Clerics competing for a BattleCleric role - they'd freak out. Yet, the Cleric capabilities of Paladins and Clerics is a lot closer than these capabilities between Warriors and Paladins.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Unlike the Warriors advantages Knights sucessfully petitioned SoE to nulify in single-group content, a Warrior can't gear up and sucessfully perform that role in harder content.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>So here we are, the universal buff recipiant in competition with a class that tanks interchanabiliy with us in all single-group content AND when grouped with a Druid MH makes the absence of a Cleric in the group virtually undectable.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>"Pulling role to protect? We lost that battle a long time ago."</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Yes, I've often watched SK's pull. In fact one SK stated their guild used SK's to pull raid content quite sucessfully. But I guess you're a Pulling Class. Get the point yet????</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>In an environment with all-single group content being able to be tanked interchangably by a</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Tank PLUS a Pulling Class PLUS a Snaring Class PLUS a Fearing Class</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>or a Tank PLUS a Buffing Class PLUS a Ressing Class PLUS a Healing Class PLUS a Root CC/stun mitigation Class</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>or the only&nbsp;Tank with avoidance/mitigation disciplines - nm strike that. with Defensive - nm unneeded, with hrrrrrm errr ahhhh lacking the ability to help restore his own HP's during combat!!</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Why would anyone in their right mind choose a Warrior or play one?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Knights will often make a huge deal over the mythological Bazaar Warrior supposedly out tanking a mighty tower of Tanking Meatyness like yerself. But they don't think it odd at all that a naked level 60 Paladin can buff others and recover HP's better than I can&nbsp;and a naked 60 SK can out pull me in most zones.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Interchangability in the Warrior class sole focus in single-group content and overwhelming unbridgable superiority in other abilities that taken alone get people invited into groups.</DIV><p>Message Edited by Battleblade-Xegony on <span class=date_text>06-27-2005</span> <span class=time_text>09:37 PM</span>	
