		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			I doubt it really requires a new thread, but, I would think by far the easiest place for a warrior to solo at level 70 would be c1 in the plane of fire.  At least in the case of BB, who's said a number of times he tries to solo in tower of sol ro.  Mobs here are similar difficulty to that, but come in singles.  Really, anyone can single pull trash throughout the zone, no special abilities are needed because aggro ranges are so tiny.  None of the guards in either castle run, and few, if any, of the rest of the zone does, either, nor have I ever witnessed a caster gate there.<br><br>In addition to that, for pulling in groups, it is rare that splitting mobs is required in MPG.  I've witnessed pallies pulling for hours in this zone without bringing a single add.  That does depend on which camp you're at, although even camps with a large number of mobs... you can usually just wait a minute for pathing to line up right, and snag a single.  For example- the snake spawn, it's usually faster to wait for the wandering spawn to move to the far side, and snag the static spawn single, than it is to try to feign split.  6-way camp is the same way.  RSS- at a lot of camps, most things can easily be singled, some pulls double, with the exception of some named spawns.  KT- except for inside the temples, most wandering trash can be singled.  Mobs on the exterior of the temples can be pulled in 1's or 2's.  2's are rarely a problem in groups, and often desirable, just because it keeps exp flowing faster than taking the time to split them (unless you have lulls, like bard and monk pullers).
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=175692" target=new>Josahd, Scourge Knight</a>
							</div>
								
